title: The Football Four Podcast breaks down an amazing Week 7
text:
Michigan State quarterback Connor Cook (18) and teammates were on the positive end of one of the most shocking endings to an FBS game in memory. (Photo: Tony Ding, AP)
CONNECT 1 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE The Gift Six. Fail to the Victors.
USA TODAY Sports college football reporters George Schroeder and Dan Wolken analyze the climax of Michigan State-Michigan and what the outcome means for each team.
In addition, they discuss the most improved aspect of Alabama and where the Crimson Tide need to see improvement, and launch into a broader discussion of just how good the SEC West actually is.
Follow the road to the 2015 College Football Playoff at The Football Four , our home to rate and debate the nation's best. And what about Memphis? If the Tigers can win week to week and remain undefeated, how far can they go?
You can listen or subscribe to the podcast on iTunes or SoundCloud below, as well as on Stitcher . We'd like to hear your comments on any of those platforms, and if you have a college football question you'd like us to discuss on the podcast, email us at footballfour@usatoday.com or follow us on Twitter @TheFootballFour .
